      • flatMap

        public static OptionalInt flatMap(OptionalInt optional,
                                  IntFunction<OptionalInt> mapper)
        If a value is present, apply the provided OptionalInt-bearing mapping function to it, return that result, otherwise return an empty OptionalInt. This method is similar to map(OptionalInt, IntToIntFunction), but the provided mapper is one whose result is already an OptionalInt, and if invoked, flatMap does not wrap it with an additional OptionalInt.
        Parameters:
        optional - optional value
        mapper - a mapping function to apply to the value, if present the mapping function
        Returns:
        the result of applying an OptionalInt-bearing mapping function to the value of this OptionalInt, if a value is present, otherwise an empty OptionalInt
